The paper discusses the theory of computational complexity and its application in various areas such as computational biology, linguistics, VLSI design, and learning theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, given the focus on understanding the contribution of various parameters to the running time of algorithms and the complexity of computational tasks, cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely sub-categories.
